3 NEW SECTION. SECTION 1. PROHIBITION ON FOREIGN NATIONAL INTERFERENCE IN STATEWIDE BALLOT
4 ISSUES. (1) IT IS UNLAWFUL FOR A FOREIGN NATIONAL, DIRECTLY OR THROUGH AN INTERMEDIARY, TO MAKE A
5 DISBURSEMENT FOR AN ELECTIONEERING COMMUNICATION, A CONTRIBUTION, OR AN EXPENDITURE, OR TO MAKE AN
6 EXPRESS OR IMPLIED PROMISE TO MAKE A CONTRIBUTION OR AN EXPENDITURE, IN CONNECTION WITH ANY STATEWIDE
7 BALLOT ISSUE.
8 (2) IT IS UNLAWFUL FOR A PERSON TO:
9 (A) SOLICIT, ACCEPT, OR RECEIVE ANY FUNDS FROM A FOREIGN NATIONAL FOR ANY PURPOSE DESCRIBED
10 IN SUBSECTION (1); OR
11 (B) MAKE A CONTRIBUTION, EXPENDITURE, OR INDEPENDENT EXPENDITURE USING ANY FUNDS THE PERSON
12 KNOWS WERE RECEIVED FROM A FOREIGN NATIONAL FOR ANY PURPOSE DESCRIBED IN THIS SECTION.
13 (3) (A) UPON RECEIPT OF A CONTRIBUTION BY A POLITICAL COMMITTEE CREATED TO SUPPORT OR TO
14 OPPOSE A BALLOT ISSUE, THE COMMITTEE TREASURER SHALL OBTAIN FROM THE DONOR AN AFFIRMATION THAT THE
15 DONOR IS NOT A FOREIGN NATIONAL.
16 (B) RECORDS OF THE DONOR AFFIRMATION RECEIVED MUST BE INCLUDED IN THE TREASURER'S
17 RECORDKEEPING OBLIGATIONS UNDER 13-37-207 AND 13-37-208.
